{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, assume (36) holds, and let φ t ∈ Aut(N) be determined by exp(tD) ∈ Aut(𝔫).",
    "By the same computations as above, the Ricci soliton equation is satisfied for the vector field X generated by φ t. □Example A.3.",
    "If N is the three-dimensional Heisenberg Lie group of 3 × 3 upper-triangular real matrices with 1's on the diagonal, then any left-invariant metric is a nilsoliton.",
    "Indeed, from [Mil76] there is an orthonormal basis {e 1, e 2, e 3 } of 𝔫 with [e 1, e 2] = 2c e 3, and the Ricci endomorphism is given byh -1 Ric h = -3c 2 Id + 2c 2 diag(1, 1, 2), diag(1, 1, 2) ∈ Der(𝔫).We call the derivation D ∈ Der(𝔫) from (36) the soliton derivation.",
    "This derivation has a number of properties arising from the GIT applications to this setting."
  ]
}